			<description><![CDATA[<h2 style="color: rgb(60, 148, 48);">
Who We Are</h2>
<p>
We are a strategic consulting and investment banking firm headquartered in Los Angeles, with offices in New York.</p>
<p>
We conduct market research, prepare business plans, and represent our clients to financial and strategic investors and acquirers.<br />
<br />
As we are currently in a high growth mode, we are looking for the right individuals to contribute to and participate in our Company expansion.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 style="color: rgb(60, 148, 48);">
The Position</h2>
<p>
We are seeking extraordinary individuals to apply analytical rigor, exceptional communication skills, and impressive client management acumen to client engagements.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
In this role you would be working in a pro-active team environment, delivering value on client projects through critical research and analytics.</p>
<p>
As a core member of our delivery team, you would have the opportunity to lead components of engagements and quickly engagements as a whole.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
We pride ourselves on a collaborative, fast-paced work environment, which is both professional and informal.</p>
<p>
Our clients are the cutting edge emerging and middle market companies of the 21st Century, and we have developed unique client relationship and engagement management processes &nbsp;to serve them and to participate in their growth.</p>
<h2 style="color: rgb(60, 148, 48);">
Qualifications</h2>
<ul>
<li>
A deep and abiding passion for business and entrepreneurship and its place in effecting meaningful change for the better in the world</li>
<li>
Proven client management skills with an enthusiastic, entrepreneurial, client service-oriented attitude and personality</li>
<li>
Extraordinary verbal and written communication skills</li>
<li>
Ability to work independently yet also thrive within a team</li>
<li>
Strong financial modeling/Excel skills</li>
<li>
Attention to detail combined with strategic aptitude</li>
<li>
Relevant work experience in management consulting, investment banking, corporate development, or an analytics-based or communications-based functional role</li>
<li>
Strong character and commitment to outstanding results in everything you do</li>
<li>
4-Year Degree required, advanced degree(s) helpful. Degrees with high quant, research, and/or written requirements preferred.</li>
<li>
Residential proximity to our LAX office (Century Blvd.) location</li>
</ul>
<h2 style="margin-top: 10px; color: rgb(60, 148, 48);">
Compensation</h2>
<ul>
<li>
Market competitive initial compensation comprised of base salary and variable target bonus; bonuses based on engagement effectiveness, efficiency, and profitability, client satisfaction, contributions to the firm, and overall company performance</li>
</ul>
